snippet.textDisplay: Revisited this after many moons! Still feel the same goosebumps as I did the first I heard it on MTV when it was released. Remember Master Saleem pointing his index finger up in the tarana when he hits the high note. Clinton Cerejo is extremely underappreciated. This was the first time I heard these dohas of Kabir and it was mind completely blown. As a fusion it does not get better than this. I would go out on an arm and leg and say this probably stands at par with Kandisa from Indian Ocean. The final tarana is definitely beautiful, but the following double bass creates a calm n soothing soundscape to consider the words of Kabir and the energy of Master Saleem. Thank you for this beautiful composition Clinto Cerejo!
